{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Place pork belly in a casserole dish or roasting tin and set aside.","Place garlic cloves, 30 g soy sauce and sesame oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>8 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Pour over pork belly, rub mixture into pork belly then roast for 50-55 minutes (180°C). Increase oven temperature to 220°C and roast for a further 10-15 minutes. Meanwhile, continue with recipe.","Place 1500 g water in mixing bowl and bring to a boil <nobr>15 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add ramen noodles and cook for <nobr>time indicated on packet\/100°C\/\/speed <\/nobr>. Drain noodles through Varoma dish and reserve cooking water in a bowl. Place noodles in a bowl and set aside.","Place bowl with hot cooking water onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in baby spinach. Leave baby spinach in hot cooking water for 2 minutes, drain spinach leaves through simmering basket and set aside. Clean mixing bowl.","Place chicken broth, 500 g water, 30 g Japanese soy sauce, ginger, 1 tsp black rice vinegar and paprika powder in mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position, add 2 eggs, close Varoma lid and cook <nobr>25 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove Varoma, rinse eggs under running water or place in cold water to cool down, then peel eggs and cut in half.","Divide reserved cooked ramen noodles between 4 soup bowls. Slice roasted pork belly and arrange on top of noodles, along with cooked baby spinach, half an egg, 3 nori seaweed sheets and 1 Tbsp sweetcorn kernels in each soup bowl. Pour over hot broth and serve hot garnished with spring onion slices and toasted sesame seeds."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["400 g pork belly meat, boned, without rind","3 garlic cloves","60 g Japanese soy sauce","10 g sesame oil","2000 g water","375 g dried ramen noodles","100 g fresh baby spinach","750 g chicken broth","20 g fresh root ginger, peeled, cut in round slices (2 mm)","1 tsp black vinegar","½ tsp hot paprika","2 medium eggs","12 nori seaweed sheets (9 cm x 3.5 cm)","4 Tbsp tinned sweetcorn","2 spring onions, cut in thin slices, to garnish","2 tsp toasted sesame seeds"]}],"id":"r211758","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-iBhYOE6LEKk\/XZMyGWpXnJI\/AAAAAAAAagc\/GW6VP87ySEIuzpM7WlbWutJG6Nxsh8pmQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_4-vL2BfEha10EmlO.png","title":"Japanese Ramen Noodle Soup","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"66 g","fat":"50 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"88 g","calories":"4507 kJ \/ 1077 kcal"},"usefulItems":"casserole dish, oven","basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 40m","4 portions"]}